article.headline: (19) TCU 62, WISC GREEN BAY 51
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wisconsin (Ticker) -- Sandora Irvin scored a 
game-high 24 points to lead No.19 TCU past Wisconsin-Green Bay,
62-51.

Irvin, who also added 18 rebounds and 7 blocked shots, shot
11-for-16 from the field to help the Lady Frogs (6-0) to their
best start in school history.

Ebony Shaw added 12 points for TCU, which led 28-27 at the half
before going on a 12-2 run midway through the second half to
give the Lady Frogs a 51-40 lead with 7:42 left.

TCU which outrebounded the Phoenix (5-2) 43-28 overall
controlled the boards in the second half by a 25-9 margin.

Natalie Yudt and Mary Kulenkamp each scored 12 points for
Wisconsin-Greenbay, which scored only one field goal over the
final 6:25, and lost back to back home games for the first time
since the 1998-1999 season.
